# 🛒 Customer Segmentation Project

## 📌 Objective
The objective of this project is to analyze customer behavior and segment customers based on their income and spending patterns using data analysis and machine learning techniques.

---

## 📂 Dataset
- Dataset used: Mall Customers Dataset
- Contains customer details such as:
  - Customer ID
  - Gender
  - Age
  - Annual Income
  - Spending Score

---

## 🛠️ Tools & Technologies Used
- Python
- Pandas
- NumPy
- Matplotlib
- Scikit-learn

---

## 🔄 Steps Performed

### 1. Data Loading
- Loaded dataset using Pandas

### 2. Data Cleaning
- Checked for missing values
- Removed unnecessary data

### 3. Feature Selection
- Selected important features:
  - Age
  - Annual Income
  - Spending Score

### 4. Data Preprocessing
- Applied StandardScaler for feature scaling

### 5. Clustering
- Used K-Means clustering algorithm
- Segmented customers into different groups

### 6. Data Visualization
- Created 2D scatter plots
- Created 3D visualization of customer segments

---

## 📊 Key Insights
- High income & high spending customers are premium customers
- Low spending customers need marketing strategies
- Customer segmentation helps businesses target the right audience

---

## 📈 Results
- Successfully segmented customers into different clusters
- Identified target customer groups

---

## 📌 Conclusion
This project helps businesses understand customer behavior and improve marketing strategies using data-driven insights.

---

## 🚀 Future Improvements
- Add more features for better accuracy
- Build a recommendation system
- Deploy using Streamlit

